      <h1 style="font-size:2.25rem;margin-top:1rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem">The Best Reciprocating Saws for Cutting Trees, Limbing and Storm Cleanup (2026)</h1>
      <div style="color:#64748b;font-size:0.9rem">June 19, 2026 &middot; 10 min read</div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>Tree limbing puts a reciprocating saw through a test that demolition work does not. You are reaching overhead on a ladder, cutting green wood saturated with moisture, and often working one-handed while holding a branch. A saw that stalls under load or vibrates so hard your forearm cramps after ten minutes is a liability, not a tool. Arborists, tree service crews, and contractors who handle storm cleanup need three things: a stroke length that clears wet sawdust fast, a blade clamp that accepts pruning-specific blades, and a weight-to-power ratio that does not punish the user during extended overhead cuts. This guide covers seven saws that deliver on all three.</p>

      <h2>What to Look for in a Tree-Cutting Reciprocating Saw</h2>
      <p>Cutting green wood is fundamentally different from cutting dimensional lumber or demolition debris. Live tree branches contain moisture that clogs standard demolition blades within seconds. The sawdust from green wood is wet and heavy, packing the blade gullet and slowing the cut. A pruning blade with 4 to 6 teeth per inch and wide gullets clears debris more effectively than finer-toothed demolition blades. On the saw side, a stroke length of at least 1-1/8 inch pulls the blade through thick branches faster, and a brushless motor maintains torque as the battery voltage drops. Orbital action, which rocks the blade into the cut on the forward stroke, can double cutting speed in green wood. Variable speed triggers give you control for starting a cut on a curved branch surface without kickback.</p>

      <h2>Best Overall Cordless: Milwaukee M18 FUEL SAWZALL 2722-20</h2>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07SD3L2VF?tag=sciencesolved-20">Milwaukee M18 FUEL SAWZALL 2722-20</a> sets the standard for cordless reciprocating saws in tree work. The POWERSTATE brushless motor delivers up to 3,000 strokes per minute with a 1-1/8-inch stroke length that powers through 8-inch limbs without bogging down. The REDLINK PLUS intelligence system regulates power delivery under load, maintaining cutting speed as the battery drains. At 6.8 pounds with battery, it is balanced enough for one-handed overhead cutting when you are reaching into a tree canopy. The tool-free blade clamp accepts standard 1/2-inch shank blades and releases with one hand even with gloves on. The anti-vibration mechanism reduces handle vibration by 30 percent compared to previous generations, which translates directly to less forearm fatigue during extended storm cleanup sessions. With over 3,800 ratings at 4.7 stars, this is the most reviewed professional-grade cordless reciprocating saw on the market. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07SD3L2VF?tag=sciencesolved-20">Check current price on Amazon</a>.</p>

