      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00N5FLVM8?tag=sciencesolved-20">DEWALT 12 Amp Reciprocating Saw (DW304)</a> has been the go-to corded saw for professional tree crews for over a decade. With 3,899 ratings at 4.8 stars, it is the highest-reviewed reciprocating saw on Amazon. The 12-amp motor delivers consistent torque through variable speed control, and the 1-1/8-inch stroke length rips through wet branches efficiently. The four-position blade clamp rotates for flush cutting against trunks and in tight crotches. Keyless blade changes work with gloved hands. Corded operation means zero battery anxiety during a full day of storm cleanup cutting through oak, maple, and pine limbs. The main trade-off is mobility: you need a generator or extension cord on site. At 8.6 pounds, it is heavier than cordless options, but the unlimited runtime is worth the weight penalty when you spend an entire shift cutting fallen trees. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00N5FLVM8?tag=sciencesolved-20">See latest pricing on Amazon</a>.</p>

