      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BCNS8L58?tag=sciencesolved-20">Bosch CRS180B 18V Lithium-Ion Reciprocating Saw</a> offers two speed ranges (0-2,400 and 0-2,700 SPM) that match cutting speed to branch density. At 17.7 inches long and 6.35 pounds, it is compact enough for reaching into tight branch crotches. The Lockjaw tool-less blade change system works one-handed with gloves. The 1-1/8-inch stroke provides efficient material removal in green wood. For tree service contractors who already own Bosch CORE18V batteries, the bare-tool format saves significant cost. The CRS180B handles limbs up to 6 inches thick with a sharp pruning blade, and the variable speed trigger eases into cuts on curved branch surfaces without kickback. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BCNS8L58?tag=sciencesolved-20">View discounts on Amazon</a>.</p>

      <h2>Best Value Corded: Craftsman V20 Cordless Reciprocating Saw Kit</h2>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07XQV1ZTB?tag=sciencesolved-20">Craftsman V20 Reciprocating Saw Cordless Kit with Oscillating Tool</a> bundles a reciprocating saw and oscillating multi-tool in one package. The reciprocating saw features a 1-inch stroke with variable speed trigger and keyless blade change. Homeowners and light contractor crews handling occasional tree trimming and property maintenance will find the V20 platform provides adequate power for branches up to 4 inches thick. The included oscillating tool adds flush-cutting capability for trimming branches flush with a trunk or fence line. The V20 battery system shares compatibility with over 200 Craftsman tools. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07XQV1ZTB?tag=sciencesolved-20">Check current price on Amazon</a>.</p>

